text:
Greetings, everyone.
PyCon India will be held in Hyderabad this year from Oct 5-9.
I have created the initial draft [here](https://github.com/sidhantnagpal/pycon-sympy/wiki/PyCon-India-2018-Proposal) for the proposal. We can make the changes here and when the initial draft is complete we can move it to SymPy wiki for review.
Deadline for submitting the proposal is July 1.
Lets complete the proposal by Jun 25.
Interested developers can add their names to the linked wiki (it is editable).

html: Hi @sidhantnagpal , I think PyCon India will expect something new. Find out new features of SymPy and SymEngine . Add them into proposal, that will look different from previous years talk/workshops. We will be selling the tickets for workshop/talk using our proposal, so think about why people will come for the workshop/talk, explore current requirements and improve the proposal accordingly.
